# README

## Steps to Set Up and Run the Table Recovery Project

### 1. Git Clone the Repository
1.1. Create a folder named "WhateverName" in any location you prefer.  
1.2. This directory will be referred to as `your_path`. It should be something like `C:/Users/..../WhateverName`.  
1.3. Run the following command to clone the repository:
```bash
git clone https://github.com/hussseinhaiadr6/TableRecovery.git
2. Set Up Virtual Environment
2.1. You may need to install virtualenv by running:

bash
Copy code
pip install virtualenv
2.2. Ensure you have Python 3.9 installed.
2.3. The path to the Python 3.9 executable should look like C:/Users/.../Python39/python.exe.
2.4. Create a virtual environment in your_path:

bash
Copy code
virtualenv -p C:/Users/HHR6/AppData/Local/Programs/Python/Python39/python.exe C:/Users/..../WhateverName/your_env_name
3. Activate the Virtual Environment
3.1. Activate the environment by navigating to the scripts folder and running the activation script:

bash
Copy code
cd C:/Users/..../WhateverName/your_env_name/scripts/
activate
4. Install Required Packages
4.1. Change the directory to where the requirements file is located:

bash
Copy code
cd C:/Users/..../WhateverName/TableRecovery
4.2. Install the required packages:

bash
Copy code
pip install -r requirements.txt
5. Clone PaddleOCR Repository
5.1. Navigate to the project directory:

bash
Copy code
cd C:/Users/..../WhateverName/TableRecovery
5.2. Clone the PaddleOCR repository:

bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/PaddlePaddle/PaddleOCR.git
6. Update Pipeline.py
6.1. In the Pipline.py file, update the input_filename variable to point to your PDF file:

python
Copy code
input_filename = "C:/Users/.../File.pdf"
7. Run the Pipeline
7.1. Execute the pipeline script:

bash
Copy code
python Pipline.py
This should run the pipeline and process your PDF file.

